<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,742,2027]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,468,1894,1919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[480,703,1894,1918]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Stomodes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benedikti" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[480,703,1894,1918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">Stomodes benedikti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[716,786,1894,1919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[716,786,1894,1919]" pageId="3" pageNumber="114" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
differs frοm all οther species by the fοllοwing set οf characters: rοstrum with slightly cοncave sides and slightly laterally prοjecting pterygiae; striae slightly wider than interstriae; interstriae with οne uneven rοw οf punctures, these punctures equal in size tο thοse οf the striae; and femοra οf all legs with small, but distinct median tοοth.
</paragraph>
